definition: little white mouse (esp. laboratory animal)/fig. guinea pig, i.e. human participant in experiment
sb or sth detested by all/target of scorn/anathema/cf. 老鼠過街，人人喊打|老鼠过街，人人喊打[lao3 shu3 guo4 jie1 , ren2 ren2 han3 da3]
lit. to refrain from shooting at the rat for fear of breaking the vases (idiom)/to not act against an evil so as to prevent harm to innocents
to cover one's head and sneak away like a rat (idiom); to flee ignominiously

sentences.english: The OSM transgenic retinal cells underwent apoptosis indicated by TUNEL assays.
sentences.chinese: TUNEL試驗顯示轉基因鼠視網膜細胞凋亡。

sentences.english: His head was kind of pinched on top like a deer's, and he had beady eyes like a rat.
sentences.chinese: 他的頭頂很尖，像鹿一樣還有像鼠一樣的豆子眼。

sentences.english: It may have been a water-rat I speared.
sentences.chinese: 哦，我踩到了什麼？那或許曾是隻麝香鼠。

sentences.english: Grandma mouse also shouted, …… . But Jules did not care.
sentences.chinese: 鼠奶奶也發出了陣陣驚叫聲，這一家子簡直亂了套。

sentences.english: Dolphins and porpoises are less vulnerable and will still be rescued.
sentences.chinese: 相比之下，更爲堅強的海豚和鼠海豚是可以被營救的。

sentences.english: Rat harm was not the inevitable outcome of its existence, but man-made.
sentences.chinese: 鼠之成害，非鼠存在之原狀，乃人爲所致。

sentences.english: The serum cholesterols of the force-fed rats only were positively increased most probably from exogenous sources.
sentences.chinese: 塡食鼠血清內膽固醇增加，可能源於食物。

sentences.english: This is a first report that Lyme disease spirochete isolated from Rattus coxingi in the whole world.
sentences.chinese: 從白腹鼠分離出萊姆病螺旋體，在國內外屬首次報告。

sentences.english: The left side of my face is so swollen makes me look like a chipmunk, and I can't stop drooling.
sentences.chinese: 可是現在我左臉腫得像只金花鼠，還不停地流口水。

sentences.english: Countryside characters, Ed and Edwina Hedgehog, Tom Mouse, Sam Rabbit and Badger.
sentences.chinese: 農村字符，教育署及派駐刺蝟，湯姆鼠，黃兔，獾。

sentences.english: The weasels killed all but four of the 100 chipmunks in this population.
sentences.chinese: 這羣的100個金花鼠被黃鼠狼獵食得只剩下4只。

sentences.english: Objective To understand the killing effect of the "Rodent target", a biochemical rodenticide.
sentences.chinese: 目的瞭解“鼠靶”生化滅鼠劑現場滅鼠效果。

sentences.english: Methods The captured mice were classified and the density was calculated.
sentences.chinese: 方法夾夜法捕鼠，計算鼠密度，確定鼠類的種羣構成。

sentences.english: Conclusion The infection of virulent strain of mouse poxvirus exists in experimental mice.
sentences.chinese: 結論實驗用昆明小鼠中存在鼠痘病毒強毒株感染。

sentences.english: They took with them dogs, rats and plants like the sweet potato.
sentences.chinese: 他們帶着他們的狗，鼠以及象山芋之類的植物。

definition: lower form of animal life, including insects, insect larvae, worms and similar creatures/CL:條|条[tiao2],隻|只[zhi1]/(fig.) person with a particular undesirable characteristic
